President Obama and Prime Minister Cameron of the United Kingdom had a phone call to discuss various global issues. They talked about the situation in Syria and agreed to work together to pressure the Assad regime and support a transition to democracy. They also discussed Somalia and the upcoming London Conference on Somalia. The President praised the Prime Minister's leadership on this issue. They also talked about the transition in Afghanistan and the situation in the eurozone, particularly in Greece. Lastly, they reviewed the preparations for Prime Minister Cameron's official visit to Washington, D.C. on March 13-14, where he and Mrs. Cameron will be welcomed by President and Mrs. Obama.